contentrichtext.text: {{TOC right}} '''[[UFO]]''' is an unidentified flying object, a popular term for any aerial phenomenon that cannot be identified. '''UFO''' may also refer to: *[[UFOs in fiction]] ==Clubs== *[[Ufo (Club, Berlin)]], the first Acid House club in Berlin *[[UFO Club]], an underground club in London, frequented in the late 1960s by Pink Floyd ==Computer technology== *[[Comparison_of_graphics_file_formats|.ufo]], a graphics file format suffix standing for '''U'''lead '''F'''ile for '''O'''bjects *.ufo, a directory format suffix standing for '''U'''nified '''F'''ont '''O'''bject (see [http://www.unifiedfontobject.org/ www.unifiedfontobject.org)] *UFO, an acronym for '''U'''ser Level '''F'''ile '''O'''rganizer ==Film and television== *[[UFO (1956 film)|''UFO'' (1956 film)]], 1956 film directed by Winston Jones *[[U.F.O. (1993 film)|''U.F.O.'' (1993 film)]], a 1993 film starring Roy "Chubby" Brown *[[U.F.O. (2012 film)|''U.F.O.'' (2012 film)]], a 2012 movie directed by Dominic Burns starring Bianca Bree, Sean Brosnan, and Jean-Claude Van Damme *[[UFO (TV series)|''UFO'' (TV series)]], a 1970s TV series *''[[UFO Ultramaiden Valkyrie]]'', a 2000s manga and anime TV series ==Games== ===Arcade games=== *[[Claw vending machine]], also known as UFO, a type of arcade game known as a merchandiser ===Computer games and videogames=== *''UFO'' game series, based on ''X-COM: UFO Defense'': **''[[X-COM: UFO Defense|UFO: Enemy Unknown]]'', also known as ''X-COM: UFO Defense'', the first game in MicroProse's ''X-COM'' series **''[[UFO: Aftermath]]'', released in 2003 **''[[UFO: Aftershock]]'', released in 2005 **''[[UFO: Afterlight]]'', released in 2007 *''[[UFO: A Day in the Life]]'', a 1999 puzzle game by Love-de-Lic *''[[UFO: Alien Invasion]]'', a free software game similar to ''X-COM: UFO Defense'' *''[[UFO: Extraterrestrials]]'', a 2007 turn-based tactics video game by Chaos Concept *''[[UFO Interactive Games]]'', an American video game company *''[[UFO Kamen Yakisoban]]'', a 1994 beat 'em up game released for the Super Famicom *''[[Undefined Fantastic Object]]'', the twelfth official game in the Japanese ''Touhou'' series *''UFOs'', a 1997 adventure game by [[Artech Entertainment, Ltd.|Artech]] ==Music== ===Artists and bands=== *[[UFO (band)]], an English hard rock band *[[UFO (musician)]], a Danish hip hop artist, rapper and singer **[[UFO & Yepha]], Danish hip hop duo comprising UFO and Yepha *[[United Future Organization]], a Japanese jazz duo *[[JLS]] ('''J'''ack the '''L'''ad '''S'''wing), an English boyband previously known as UFO ===Works=== *[[UFO (composition)|''UFO'' (composition)]], a concert band work composed by Michael Daugherty *[[Ufoetry]], a multimedia UFO rock opera ===Songs=== *"UFO", a 1981 song by [[ESG (band)|ESG]], from their debut self-titled EP *[[UFO (Pink Lady song)|"UFO" (Pink Lady song)]] *[[UFO (Sneaky Sound System song)|"UFO" (Sneaky Sound System song)]] *[[U.F.O. (song)|"U.F.O." (Coldplay song)]] ==Other uses== *[[UFO (ride)]], an amusement park ride *[[Float (breakdancing move)#Variants|UFO]], a breakdancing move *''[[Ufo abei]]'', the sole species of gall wasp in the genus ''Ufo'' *''[[UFOs: The Greatest Stories]]'', a short-story anthology by Martin H. Greenberg *[[United Farmers of Ontario]], a political party that formed the government in Ontario, Canada from 1919 to 1923 *[[UHF Follow-On System]], a US DoD communications satellite constellation *Ultra-fast outflows, a mechanism by which active galactic nuclei may feed matter back into their host galaxy *[[used frying oil]], is used for producing used frying oil methyl ester (ufome), see also [[Fatty acid methyl ester]] ==See also== *[[Flying saucer (disambiguation)]] {{Disambiguation}}
